caption.text:
Happy Independence day my dearest nation. Despite the fact, that I might not be able to celebrate the Independence day back in my hometown, but my heart and soul will always be Indonesian. For centuries, our nation had envision for a strong, inpendent yet civilized and a nation with a unique character. Hence we held that believe and yet we barely reached the nation our forfathers wished. Despite, the effort of the goverment, we as  Indonesian still being apathetic of our nation condition. I hereby as a fellow Indonesian to urge our fellow comrade, to join hands and to fight radicalism and exteimism and defend our Ideology and together rebuild the nation that was once being shattered by vested interest either by race, culture or background. May God bless thus nation, long live Indonesia. .
.
Digahayu Indonesiaku yg ke 72
Meskipun tidak mampu bereda di bumi pertiwi untuk mengingat jasa pahlawan yang rela melepaskan segalanya, demi sang merah putih dikibarkan dan diakui oleh dunia international.Tetap semangat dan terus saling bahu membahu untuk membangun persatuan berdasarkan nilai ideoligi kita yaitu Pancasila, bersatu untuk menumpas radikalisme dan terorisme, dan bergotong royong untuk membangun masa depan Indonesia yang adil, makmur, dan berkepribadian. 🇲🇨🇲🇨🇲🇨

caption.text:
Long live Indonesia (Dirgahayu Indonesiaku) 
It's been 71 years since this nation declared it's independence... My deepest gratitude to the fighters, who were willing to sacrifice everything even their own life, just for  one yet important word: FREEDOM !!! 😲
Hopefully Indonesia will continue to implement its policies in accordance with the Nawacita (9 points of hope) and Trisakti (3 main policy points)....
In the future, Indonesia will DEFINITELY be a great nation, a nation that has a great character, a nation that rely on God, and respected by other nations ....
FREEDOM INDONESIA !!!! 💂💂
.
.
萬歲印尼...
從前到現在，71年都已過了...
很多戰士，已經奮鬥了所有的一切，為了這兩個詞：自由😲
希望印尼繼續按照Nawacita (九點願望政策)和Trisakti(3點政策)實施其政策....
後來肯定會成為一個偉大的國家，有個性，依靠神，而且能得到國家的尊重....
自由，印度尼西亞!!!!💂💂

It all started when I was having in the Cafe. 🏠🍗
I ordered Cheese Panini Sandwich and Waffles for dessert. 😊
Then suddenly a waiter came by and gave me a cup of cold Milk Tea. 
I told him that, I didn't order a drink. But he told me, it's alright. It's for me. 
I wad surprised to hear that😲 
I didn't know, if this is their policy or maybe that waiter is really kind and generous😞😅Thank God 😇
Henceforth, that was the proof that  there was still taiwanese that was still kind and generous.... 😎😉
Anyway, I'm glad that I am studying in Taiwan😀😍
My depeest gratitude for that waiter and thank you Taiwan for showing me "Taiwan" from a different angle.....🙂
#generous #generousity #taiwan #kaoshiung #publiclibrary #cafe #dinner #sandwich
